                          linktype="simple">Lonsdale (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poems</title> (1969),  201-207</bibref>
               </bibliography>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Written probably in <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1754"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="1754/1755"
                              certainty="circa"
                              era="ce"
                              calendar="gregorian">1754 or 
							1755</date>
                     </extref>.
							First printed privately in 1774. First published, in two versions, among
							the notes to the poems, entitled <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Ode, On the
								Pleasure arising from Vicissitude</title>, and as <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Ode</title> in <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Mason, William, 1724-1797"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="Mason, William, 1724-1797">Mason</persname>'s</extref>
                     <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Memoirs</title> (<date normal="1775" type="publication" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1775</date>), <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1775&amp;part=2&amp;page=78"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">78-81</extref> (with <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Mason, William, 1724-1797"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="Mason, William, 1724-1797">Mason</persname>'s</extref> additions) and <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1775&amp;part=1&amp;page=236"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">236-237</extref> (ll. 1-48 only) respectively.
						</p>
